channel.title: CVE Feed for Synology -- Photo Station
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Synology -- Photo Station

item.title: CVE-2019-11821|2024-09-17T01:46:34.857Z -- synology -- photo%20station
item.description: SQL injection vulnerability in synophoto_csPhotoDB.php in Synology Photo Station before 6.8.11-3489 and before 6.3-2977 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary SQL command via the type parameter.

item.title: CVE-2017-12072|2024-09-17T01:36:39.715Z -- synology -- photo%20station
item.description: Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in PixlrEditorHandler.php in Synology Photo Station before 6.8.0-3456 allows remote authenticated users to inject arbitrary web scripts or HTML via the id parameter.

item.title: CVE-2017-16772|2024-09-17T04:23:49.491Z -- synology -- photo%20station
item.description: Improper input validation vulnerability in SYNOPHOTO_Flickr_MultiUpload in Synology Photo Station before 6.8.3-3463 and before 6.3-2971 allows remote authenticated users to execute arbitrary codes via the prog_id parameter.

item.title: CVE-2015-9102|2024-09-17T03:14:38.172Z -- synology -- photo%20station
item.description: Multiple cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities in Synology Photo Station 6.0 before 6.0-2638 and 6.3 before 6.3-2962 allow remote authenticated attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via the (1) album name, (2) file name of uploaded photos, (3) description of photos, or (4) tag of the photos.

item.title: CVE-2019-11822|2024-09-17T02:41:18.093Z -- synology -- photo%20station
item.description: Relative path traversal vulnerability in SYNO.PhotoStation.File in Synology Photo Station before 6.8.11-3489 and before 6.3-2977 allows remote attackers to upload arbitrary files via the uploadphoto parameter.
